Step 1: Calculate Quick Assets
• Cash on Hand: 2,179,154.14  
• Bank Deposits: 2,952,150.00  
• Interest Receivable: 9,881.70  
• Accounts Receivable: 200,359.99  
Quick Assets = 2,179,154.14 + 2,952,150.00 + 9,881.70 + 200,359.99 = 5,341,545.83

Step 2: Get Current Liabilities
From the balance sheet, Total Current Liabilities = 5,042,389.63

Step 3: Calculate Quick Ratio
Quick Ratio = Quick Assets / Current Liabilities  
= 5,341,545.83 / 5,042,389.63 ≈ 1.06

Step 4: Calculate Net Profit Margin
From the income statement:  
Net Profit = 56,497.85  
Total Revenue = 547,392.30  
Net Profit Margin = (Net Profit / Total Revenue) × 100  
= (56,497.85 / 547,392.30) × 100 ≈ 10.32%

Thus, the final answer is:

{
  "solution": {
    "Quick Ratio": "1.06",
    "Net Profit Margin": "10.32%"
  }
}
